<dl id="n10114c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10114c">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10114c"> 114(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">D</font> burns letters</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;<mark>Destroying letters</mark>,&rdquo; he remarked, &ldquo;is sometimes a pity.&rdquo; &hellip; &ldquo;I used to write, in detail, to my fianc&eacute;e of my Milan experiences: my thoughts and labors, everything, I believe, which happened to me in which she would be interested. And in some way, shortly before our marriage, they were destroyed. I&apos;ve often wished I had them now.&rdquo; <small> Pierre V.R. Key, Louis. <a name="PVRK" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#PVRK"><cite title="source">John McCormack: His own life story</cite></a> (1918) 131</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
